Subject: [PATCH 2/6] feat: implement all 8 feature enhancements

1. Crossfade curve presets: linear, logarithmic, equal-power, and
   inverse-square curves selectable from toolbar dropdown
2. Per-device mute toggle: click speaker nodes or press M to mute/unmute
   nearest speaker; muted devices show "MUTE" and are excluded from mix
3. Preset positions: save/load control point positions with curve type
   to localStorage; recall by clicking or pressing 1-9 keys
4. Device grouping: create named zones that link speakers to share the
   same volume (max of group members); visual arcs connect grouped nodes
5. WebSocket real-time sync: flask-socketio replaces HTTP polling for
   lower-latency volume updates and push-based device change notifications;
   background monitor thread detects device changes every 3s
6. Per-device EQ: bass/treble sliders (-1.0 to +1.0) stored server-side
   and synced via WebSocket; designed for integration with Equalizer APO
7. Auto-reconnect volume restore: server remembers last volume per device
   and automatically restores it when a Bluetooth speaker reconnects
8. Keyboard/accessibility: arrow keys move control point (shift for fine),
   Home centers it, Tab cycles device focus with screen reader announcements,
   M toggles mute, 1-9 loads presets; ARIA live region and roles added

Backend: 40 tests covering all new API endpoints and logic.

