From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 5 Mar 2026 23:06:11 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/6] fix: resolve bugs, race conditions, and optimize
 performance

Bugs fixed:
- Race condition: _device_groups dict emitted outside its lock in
  api_groups_create and api_groups_delete (copy inside lock now)
- Invalid CSS: group arc color used hsl() + "40" string concat producing
  broken color values; replaced with hsla() alpha parameter
- EQ sliders and group checkboxes lost user state on every 3s device
  update; panels now only re-render when the device list actually changes

Performance optimizations:
- get_playback_devices: snapshot muted/eq/groups state once before loop
  instead of acquiring 3 locks per device (O(n) lock ops -> O(1))
- Group membership lookup: replaced O(n*m) linear scan with O(1) reverse
  dict lookup built during snapshot
- set_volumes_batch: batch _volumes_lock acquisition after loop instead
  of per-device lock acquire/release
- Device monitor: replaced full json.dumps serialization with lightweight
  tuple-based snapshot key for change detection
- layoutDevices: replaced O(n^2) Array.find with O(n) Map lookup

Dead code removed:
- _MAX_PRESET_NAME_LEN, _MAX_PRESETS constants (presets are client-only)
- Unused wsIndicator DOM reference (overwritten by innerHTML)
- Unused json import (was only for monitor serialization)
- f-string with no interpolation in group validation

