Date: Thu, 5 Mar 2026 23:21:37 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] fix: security, performance, and correctness optimizations

Security:
- Fix XSS in Spotify callback by escaping error/resp.text/exc with html.escape()

Performance:
- Cache device list in audio level monitor (was re-enumerating COM 10x/sec)
- Convert device_ids to set for O(1) lookup in group creation
- DRY up 4 repetitive Spotify playback handlers into shared helper
- Remove dead code (unused `meter` variable in get_audio_levels)

Correctness:
- Fix race condition: api_spotify_now_playing now copies dict under lock
- Fix api_groups_list serializing dict under lock (copy first)
- Move audioLevels declaration near state to avoid fragile ordering
- Add audio level smoothing (fast attack/slow decay) for natural meters
- Add Spotify progress bar interpolation between 3s server updates
- Add Spotify HTTP polling fallback when WebSocket is disconnected

